ANNUAL MEETING IN WROCLAW, POLAND 2017

Librarian and Archivist of Canada, Library and Archives Canada

Election of the new Chair of the CDNL for 2018 – 2021.

9:30 – 10:50

3. Introducing the theme of the year: National Libraries Connecting Continents and Communities / Kai Ekholm

Chair: Kai Ekholm

Keynote Address

Cultural Heritage Linked Data on the Semantic Web: Infrastructures and Applications, Eero Hyvönen, Professor, University of Helsinki & Aalto University, HELDIG – Helsinki Centre for Digital Humanities, Finland

Tracing Global Information Networks in Historical Newspaper Repositories, Hannu Salmi, Professor, University of Turku, Finland

Discussion 10.50 – 11.00

4. Break 11.00– 12.30

5. IFLA Global Vision

Gerald Leitner, Secretary General, IFLA Donna Scheeder, President, IFLA Glòria Pérez-Salmerón, President-elect

For mobile voting: bring a laptop, smartphone or tablet with wireless internet access with you.

12:30-14.00 Group photo, then lunch

14.00 – 15.30

6.Digital Unification – Connecting our Documentary Heritage Chair: Guy Berthiaume, Introduction
